<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="383" pageId="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[816,1430,1684,2019]" lastBlockId="13.[159,771,223,317]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="383" pageId="12">
A single specimen was collected in the Manho forest (
<quantity box="[903,1000,1719,1745]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="12" unit="m" value="1800.0">1800 m</quantity>
) on the plateau of Mount Namuli. Previously, a single specimen was collected from Chiutu in the Zambezi Valley (
<bibRefCitation author="SMITHERS, R. H. N. &amp; J. L. P. LOBAO TELLO" pageId="12" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref14678" refString="SMITHERS, R. H. N., and J. L. P. LOBAO TELLO. 1976. Check list and atlas of the mammals of Mozambique. Museum Memoir, The Trustees of the National Museums and Monuments of Rhodesia, 8: 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1976">Smithers and Lobão Tello, 1976</bibRefCitation>
). The species has been extensively recorded across Southern Africa, as far west as 
<collectingCountry box="[816,905,1890,1916]" name="Angola" pageId="12">Angola</collectingCountry>
, and as far north as 
<collectingCountry box="[1142,1219,1890,1916]" name="Kenya" pageId="12">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="SIMMONS, N. B." box="[1234,1424,1890,1916]" pageId="12" refId="ref14542" refString="SIMMONS, N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. Pp. 313 - 529, in Mammal species of the World: a taxonomic and geographic reference, 3 rd edition (D. E. WILSON and D. M. REEDER, eds.). The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, 2142 pp." type="book" year="2005">Simmons, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="MONADJEM, A. &amp; P. J. TAYLOR &amp; F. P. D. COTTERILL &amp; M. C. SCHOEMAN" box="[816,1089,1924,1950]" pageId="12" refId="ref14234" refString="MONADJEM, A., P. J. TAYLOR, F. P. D. COTTERILL, and M. C. SCHOEMAN. 2010. Bats of Southern and Central Africa: a biogeographic and taxonomic synthesis. University of the Witwatersrand, Johannesburg, 596 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Monadjem 
<emphasis box="[951,1003,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="12">et al</emphasis>
., 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The species is often associated with mountainous terrain, including records from nearby Mount Mulanje (
<bibRefCitation author="KEARNEY, T. C. &amp; V. VAN CAKENBERGHE &amp; E. C. J. SEAMARK &amp; C. NDHLOVU &amp; L. COHEN" box="[1169,1417,1993,2019]" pageId="12" pagination="127 - 134" refId="ref13917" refString="KEARNEY, T. C., V. VAN CAKENBERGHE, E. C. J. SEAMARK, C. NDHLOVU, and L. COHEN. 2008. Notes on the taxonomy and distribution of Eptesicus hottentotus (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae) and reidentification of some museum voucher specimens. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 45: 127 - 134." type="journal article" year="2008">
Kearney 
<emphasis box="[1278,1338,1993,2019]" italics="true" pageId="12">et al.</emphasis>
, 2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Its occurrence in Afromontane forest on Mount Namuli is therefore somewhat unsurprising.
</paragraph>
